A RESOLUTION
1 Commending and congratulating James L. Davis; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, James L. Davis was born on March 31, 1923, in Lexington, Mississippi, and
3 this year he enjoys the rare distinction of celebrating his 102nd birthday; and
4 WHEREAS, as a youth, his family relocated to St. Louis, Missouri, where he was reared and
5 educated, and in 1939, he became a member of the Paramount Golf Club, the first Black golf
6 club west of the Mississippi; and
7 WHEREAS, James L. Davis served thereafter as a guardian of this nation's freedom and
8 liberty with the United States Army, valiantly and courageously protecting his fellow
9 Americans during World War II, receiving numerous awards for outstanding service, and
10 retiring at the rank of Sergeant; and
11 WHEREAS, following his honorable discharge, he worked as a member, owner, and trainer
12 at the Cahokia Downs and Fairmont Horse Racetracks in Illinois, gaining recognition as a
13 trainer extraordinaire and earning distinction on the United States Field Trial Circuit; and
