14 WHEREAS, during the Civil Rights Movement, James L. Davis was broadly recognized for
15 his leadership in bringing fair housing to Black residents in St. Louis, and he continues to
16 serve as a faithful patriarch to his church, family, and community; and
17 WHEREAS, this distinguished gentleman has given inspiration to many through his high
18 ideals, morals, and deep concern for his fellow citizens; and
19 WHEREAS, James L. Davis possesses the vast wisdom which only comes through
20 experience and the strength of character which is achieved through overcoming the many
21 challenges of life; and
22 WHEREAS, by the example James L. Davis has made of his life, he makes this world a
23 better place in which to live, and it is only fitting and proper that he be appropriately
24 recognized during this very special and memorable time.
25 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
26 the members of this body commend James L. Davis for his unselfish, dedicated, and loving
27 service to the members of his family and community; congratulate him on the remarkable
28 occasion of his 102nd birthday; and extend their most sincere best wishes for continued
29 health and happiness.
30 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
31 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to James
32 L. Davis.
